<p>I try to update the Datatables when you click the button. My JQuery code in "spr_well_types.js.coffee":</p>  <pre><code>jQuery -&gt;      sprWellTable = $('#spr_well_types').dataTable       sPaginationType: "full_numbers"       bJQueryUI: true       bProcessing: true       bServerSide: true       sAjaxSource: $('#spr_well_types').data('source')  $(document).ready -&gt;   $("#Refresh").on "click", (event) -&gt;     sprWellTable.fnDraw() </code></pre>  <p>My page "index.html.erb":</p>  <pre><code>&lt;button id="Refresh" type="button"&gt;Refresh&lt;/button&gt; &lt;table id="spr_well_types" class="display" data-source="&lt;%= spr_well_types_url(format: "json")%&gt;"&gt;   &lt;thead&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;th&gt;Name&lt;/th&gt;       &lt;th&gt;Short Name&lt;/th&gt;       &lt;th&gt;Lock version&lt;/th&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;   &lt;/thead&gt;   &lt;tbody&gt;    &lt;/tbody&gt; &lt;/table&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Code I click on the Refresh button in the browser error "ReferenceError: sprWellTable is not defined". I saw the <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/26515390/how-can-i-refresh-a-datatable-on-rails-after-an-update-action" title="theme">theme</a>, but the code:</p>  <pre><code>$("#Refresh").click -&gt;   sprWellTable.fnDraw() </code></pre>  <p>Not tied to the Refresh button.</p>